<section id="hotels">
  <title>Hotels</title>

  <p>We recommend the
  <link href="http://www.millenniumhotels.com/usa/millenniumcincinnati/">Millennium
  Hotel Cincinnati</link>. The Millennium is in the heart of downtown and is a short
  walk from streetcar stops and social events.</p>
</section>

<section id="transportation">
  <title>Getting Around</title>

  <p>Union Hall is in Cincinnatiâ€™s Over-the-Rhine (OTR) neighborhood, which borders
  the north side of downtown. Downtown and OTR are connected by the
  <link href="http://www.cincinnati-oh.gov/streetcar/">Cincinnati streetcar</link>.
  For Union Hall, use the 12th &amp; Vine stop when coming from the south, and use
  the Washington Park stop when coming from the north. Tickets are available at all
  streetcar stops. The streetcar costs $1 for a two-hour pass, or just $2 for an
  all-day pass.</p>

  <p>Use the
  <link href="http://www.go-metro.com/">Cincinnati Metro bus</link> to visit other
  parts of Cincinnati, or the
  <link href="http://www.tankbus.org/">TANK bus</link> to visit Northern Kentucky.
  <link href="http://www.cincyredbike.org/">Red Bike</link> has bicycle rental
  locations spread around Cincinnati and Nothern Kentucky.</p>

  <p>Cincinnati is served by the
  <link href="http://www.cvgairport.com/">Cincinnati/Northern Kentucky
  International Airport (CVG)</link>. Shuttles between the airport and downtown are
  available from
  <link href="http://executivetransportation.org/">Executive Transportation</link>
  for $36 roundtrip.</p>

